§CALIBRATION
target: aist-protocol-design

[C1] "section-names-to-concrete-losses"
     before: "Drops CALIBRATION section"
     after: "Loses 3 rounds of voice calibration that took 40 minutes"
     why: Users decide based on value, not labels. Abstract descriptions don't convey what was invested.

[C2] "profiles-as-filters-to-fidelity-as-dial"
     before: MINIMAL profile = skip IDEAS, IMPLEMENTATION, ARTIFACTS
     after: MIN fidelity = compressed, but you see what's lost and choose
     why: The difference is informed consent. Filter vs dial.

[C3] "rules-without-examples-are-ambiguous"
     before: "Don't use dramatic closers" (rule only)
     after: "In production that string is half the codebase." → "The string just passes through untouched." + why
     why: The pair IS the knowledge. Rules compress poorly because boundaries are gradient, not binary.

