§SIGNIFICANCE
[B1] type:breakthrough title:"Creative state transfer gap"
     insight: AIST v0.4 was built for technical decisions (binary, discrete).
     Creative work produces gradient judgments that need different primitives —
     before/after calibration pairs, self-check heuristics, and workflow mechanics.
     Discovered by trying to compress a real voice DNA session.
     impact: HIGH — led to entire v0.5 redesign

[B2] type:discovery title:"Profiles were silent information destroyers"
     insight: v0.4 profiles decided what to capture, not what to compress.
     MINIMAL didn't just compress — it never recorded IDEAS or IMPLEMENTATION.
     The fix wasn't better profiles but separating capture (always full) from transfer (fidelity dial).
     impact: HIGH — core philosophy change

[B3] type:discovery title:"Concrete loss descriptions change decisions"
     insight: "Drops CALIBRATION section" is abstract. "Loses 3 rounds of voice work that took 40 min"
     is visceral. The Transfer Budget works because it speaks in invested effort, not section names.
     impact: MEDIUM — shapes how protocol is used

